article.headline: Stony Brook 58, Albany, N.Y. 47
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. -- Chris Martin scored 20 points to lead Stony Brook to a 58-47 victory against Albany, N.Y., on Thursday night. Muhammad El-Amin added 16 points for the Seawolves (14-11, 6-6- America East). Tim Ambrose led the Great Danes (13-12, 6-7) with 14 points. Brett Gifford had 10 points for Albany, which has lost four straight. Demetrius Young's three-point play to close out the first half gave Stony Brook a 20-19 lead. Albany had its last lead, 39-38, on a tip-in by Ambrose at 9:17 of the second half. Martin's 3-pointer put Stony Brook up 41-39 at 7:16 of the second half, and the Seawolves never trailed again.
